definition: obscure and unknown (idiom); an outsider without any reputation/a nobody/an unknown quantity

sentences.english: Sometimes, it is better to remain unknown than to make pimple hate you.
sentences.chinese: 有時，保持默默無聞比讓人恨你要好得多。

sentences.english: Cheng Guorong lived unknown on the streets of Ningbo about half a month ago.
sentences.chinese: 在半個月之前，程國榮還默默無聞地生活在寧波街頭。

sentences.english: They would have continued to struggle against economic odds and would have lived in obscurity.
sentences.chinese: 他們會繼續過緊巴巴的日子，默默無聞地活着。

sentences.english: It is the unsung achiever of our prosperity.

sentences.english: Jesus Christ lived obscurely for most of his life, and never travelled far.

sentences.english: B. The star of the film is a previously unknown actor.
sentences.chinese: 這個電影裏的明星以前是個默默無聞的演員。

sentences.english: A nurse is plum tree in winter, sending fragrance in complete silence.

sentences.english: The star of the film is a previously unknown actor.

sentences.english: He's nobody here in town but I suppose he's a somebody in his own village.
sentences.chinese: 他在城裏默默無聞，我想他在本村卻非等閒之輩。

sentences.english: So, the panels worked in obscurity for decades.
sentences.chinese: 因此，審查會默默無聞地運作了幾十年。

sentences.english: In the early and middle years of his life, Whitman was obscure and rarely visited.
sentences.chinese: 惠特曼早年和中年時一直默默無聞，問者寥寥。

sentences.english: He spent most of his life working in obscurity .
sentences.chinese: 他在默默無聞的工作中度過了大半生。

sentences.english: The song remained in obscurity for two years.
sentences.chinese: 在此後的兩年裏，這首歌一直默默無聞。

sentences.english: Year after year here lives me but unnoticed.
sentences.chinese: 年復一年，我存於期間卻默默無聞。

sentences.english: Her screen career, for all practical purposes, had guttered out.
sentences.chinese: 她的銀幕生涯實際上默默無聞地結束了。

sentences.english: That oblivion, however, would not be a matter of Chiang's own choosing.
sentences.chinese: 但是蔣介石自己決不會甘心情願就此默默無聞。
